WEBVTT

00:02.756 --> 00:03.856
<i>I'm gonna see my little girl!</i>

00:03.858 --> 00:05.458
No!

00:05.460 --> 00:07.260
You're not gonna get away
with this, Frannie! You're not!

00:07.262 --> 00:09.195
You are not coming in. Christopher!
I'm... I'm...

00:09.197 --> 00:10.998
We've got an audience.
Better call for backup.

00:10.999 --> 00:12.832
12 David requesting 10-85.
No, no, not like this...

00:12.834 --> 00:15.468
No emergency. We have a crowd at this location.
I want you to listen to me.

00:15.470 --> 00:16.703
You're not gonna get away
with this, Frannie!

00:16.705 --> 00:17.804
You're not coming in!
You're not...

00:17.806 --> 00:19.539
Okay, okay.
All right, hey, hey! Excuse me.

00:19.541 --> 00:20.807
Excuse me. Calm down. What's
going on? What's the problem?

00:20.809 --> 00:22.141
I'm just trying
to see my daughter.

00:22.143 --> 00:23.843
He's trying
to take her away from me.

00:23.845 --> 00:25.545
No, I'm not!
You okay, Mommy? - Oh.

00:25.547 --> 00:27.513
Alex, Alex, come to Daddy.
Come to Daddy.

00:27.515 --> 00:28.815
Whoa. Whoa.
Come on, man.

00:28.817 --> 00:30.717
Do me a favor. Back up.
Okay, tell me your name.

00:30.719 --> 00:32.919
Christopher Collins.
I just want to talk to her.

00:32.921 --> 00:34.654
Okay, talk to me.
Do-do you live here?

00:34.656 --> 00:35.922
No, but I got rights.

00:37.525 --> 00:38.791
Who has legal custody
of this child?

00:38.793 --> 00:40.493
I do.

00:40.495 --> 00:41.628
That doesn't mean
you can keep her from me.

00:41.630 --> 00:42.829
She's my kid, too.
Okay.

00:42.831 --> 00:43.997
What do
we got?

00:43.999 --> 00:45.031
We got a domestic.

00:45.033 --> 00:46.099
Maybe you can get
Mr. Collins' side

00:46.101 --> 00:47.501
of the story, and
we'll talk to her.

00:47.835 --> 00:48.934
Hey, I didn't do anything wrong!

00:48.936 --> 00:50.169
We didn't
say you did.

00:50.171 --> 00:51.203
I didn't do anything wrong.

00:51.205 --> 00:52.304
We just want
to talk to you.

00:52.306 --> 00:55.341
Okay, how did this all
get started?

00:55.343 --> 00:57.176
It's no big deal, okay?

00:57.178 --> 00:58.244
We can work this
out ourselves.

00:58.246 --> 00:59.545
Get off me.
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

00:59.547 --> 01:00.746
Would you just get off?!
Hey, calm down!

01:00.748 --> 01:02.348
Hey, I didn't do anything

01:02.350 --> 01:04.382
wrong, man!
What the hell are you doing?!

01:04.385 --> 01:05.618
You're going in
for disorderly conduct.

01:05.620 --> 01:06.752
I didn't do anything!

01:06.754 --> 01:08.721
You're going in for
disorderly conduct.

01:08.723 --> 01:10.422
What the hell are you doing, man?!
They're hurting Daddy.

01:10.424 --> 01:12.024
It's okay. There is
no need for that. - Alex...

01:12.026 --> 01:13.492
Please. This is
a private matter.

01:13.494 --> 01:15.261
You made it a public matter

01:15.263 --> 01:17.229
when you brought it
out on the street.

01:19.066 --> 01:21.734
All you damn cops ever do
is make things worse.

01:28.575 --> 01:30.176
We respond, diffuse
the situation,

01:30.178 --> 01:32.144
and we're the bad guys?

01:32.146 --> 01:34.213
Domestics are like
a box of chocolates.

01:34.215 --> 01:36.248
You never know
what you're gonna get.

01:36.250 --> 01:38.517
Yeah, I just feel bad
for that little girl.

01:38.519 --> 01:40.986
Yeah, she didn't win the lottery
in the parent department.

01:40.988 --> 01:43.289
Yeah. Know how
that feels.

01:43.291 --> 01:45.658
Just got another letter
from my dad yesterday.

01:45.660 --> 01:48.227
He never gives up.
Here you go.

01:48.229 --> 01:50.329
Maybe you should
think about...

01:50.331 --> 01:52.364
writing him back.

01:52.366 --> 01:56.735
Trust me, that letter wouldn't
make it past the prison censors.

01:56.737 --> 01:58.837
I need some help back here!

02:00.000 --> 02:06.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:07.414 --> 02:08.881
Call for a bus!
Hey, what the hell happened?

02:08.883 --> 02:10.583
He had to take a leak.

02:10.585 --> 02:12.117
I took his cuffs off,
next thing I know,

02:12.119 --> 02:13.185
he took a swing at me.

02:13.187 --> 02:14.253
Did he bang his head?

02:14.255 --> 02:15.621
I-I don't know.

02:15.623 --> 02:17.156
Maybe he's on something.
I finally got him to the ground.

02:17.158 --> 02:18.558
Then I realized
he wasn't breathing.

02:18.559 --> 02:20.793
Eddie, give me a time check.
Hey, Christopher, stay with me.

02:20.795 --> 02:22.795
Come on, breathe.
Christopher, breathe!

02:22.797 --> 02:24.697
Hey, stay with me.

02:24.699 --> 02:27.466
Breathe. Chris,
breathe, Chris.

02:27.468 --> 02:31.036
And put a rush
on that bus!

02:33.873 --> 02:36.041
Yeah. I got it.

02:36.043 --> 02:38.143
I want the UOR on my desk

02:38.145 --> 02:40.379
before end of tour.

02:40.381 --> 02:43.782
I understand,
and the M.E.'s cause of death

02:43.784 --> 02:45.017
as soon as they can.

02:45.019 --> 02:47.987
I'll expect
to hear from you, Dino.

02:47.989 --> 02:49.021
What?

02:49.023 --> 02:51.690
We got a death in custody.

02:51.692 --> 02:53.359
12th precinct.

02:53.361 --> 02:55.561
Christopher Collins, age 34.

02:55.563 --> 02:57.429
We're gonna have
to hold a press conference.

02:57.431 --> 02:58.631
I know that, Garrett.

02:58.633 --> 03:01.533
Comes with the job.

03:01.535 --> 03:03.302
That went surprisingly well.

03:03.304 --> 03:04.436
Not my first rodeo.

03:04.438 --> 03:06.171
You should learn to
take a compliment.

03:06.173 --> 03:07.306
I'll put that
on my bucket list.

03:07.308 --> 03:08.474
Commissioner?
As you were.

03:08.476 --> 03:09.708
This press conference
is over, folks.

03:09.710 --> 03:10.809
Thanks for your time.

03:10.811 --> 03:12.211
Will Officer Cutter
be suspended?

03:12.213 --> 03:13.912
Officer Cutter's been placed
on modified assignment

03:13.914 --> 03:15.948
while this incident
is investigated.

03:15.950 --> 03:17.449
But do you take it personally

03:17.451 --> 03:20.452
when a citizen in custody
loses his life on your watch?

03:20.454 --> 03:22.321
We stand proudly on
this department's record

03:22.323 --> 03:24.290
of treating the public with
professionalism and respect.

03:24.292 --> 03:26.191
Commissioner? Commissioner?
That said,

03:26.193 --> 03:27.559
any loss of life is tragic.

03:27.561 --> 03:29.662
Mr. Collins' death will be
fully investigated

03:29.664 --> 03:31.864
by this department and
the district attorney's office.

03:31.866 --> 03:33.232
What's your reaction
to the selection

03:33.234 --> 03:34.800
of your daughter, Erin Reagan,

03:34.802 --> 03:37.403
to lead the D.A.'s investigation
of this matter?

03:38.906 --> 03:40.572
I have no comment on that.

03:40.574 --> 03:41.840
What would you say to those

03:41.842 --> 03:43.776
who will call this a glaring
conflict of interest?

03:43.778 --> 03:45.944
My daughter is
an accomplished prosecutor.

03:45.946 --> 03:48.347
And you feel she could be
objective about this, even when

03:48.349 --> 03:50.282
her father's professional
reputation is at stake?

03:50.284 --> 03:52.818
That is a question
that should be addressed to her.

03:52.820 --> 03:53.619
Exactly.

03:53.621 --> 03:54.620
But since

03:54.622 --> 03:55.688
you so ridiculously asked me,

03:55.690 --> 03:57.122
of course I think
she can be objective.

03:57.124 --> 03:58.290
That's it, Helen.

03:58.292 --> 04:00.526
- One more question.
- Commissioner?

04:01.100 --> 04:05.100
